# Local AI Workspace Cockpit — Cursor Rules

You are building a **Local AI Workspace Cockpit**: a local-first, highly secure agentic AI orchestration platform.

## Priorities

1. **Clean Architecture** — Strict separation between UI (`cockpit/`), Orchestration/Gateway (API routes), and File Execution (`workspace/projects/`).
2. **Local Sovereignty** — All artifacts, code, and logs persist under `workspace/projects/<project_slug>/`.
3. **Production-Grade Code** — Type-safe TypeScript, resilient error handling, no mock placeholders unless explicitly requested.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** Next.js App Router, React 19, Tailwind CSS, shadcn-style components
- **API:** Next.js Route Handlers (Node runtime) for filesystem + SSE telemetry
- **Storage root:** `workspace/projects/` (override via `WORKSPACE_ROOT`)

## Domain Types

All shared types live in `cockpit/src/types/cockpit.ts`:

- `AgentTask`, `ExecutionStatus`, `AgentEvent`, `ProjectFile`, `ProjectMetadata`

## File System Safety

- Sanitize paths via `resolveProjectPath()` — reject directory traversal
- Writes are scoped to `workspace/projects/`
- HITL approval required before high-risk tool execution

## Initial Scaffold (completed)

1. `cockpit/src/types/cockpit.ts` — Domain definitions
2. `cockpit/src/app/api/files/route.ts` — File tree read/write API
3. `cockpit/src/components/layout/dashboard-shell.tsx` — Three-pane dashboard

## Directory Standard

```text
workspace/
└── projects/
    └── <project_slug>/
        ├── src/
        ├── docs/
        ├── logs/
        └── metadata.json
```
